<br>
And while the Queen *is* well groomed and dressed, Moirai sees none of that. All she sees before her is exactly what she expected to see: an uncivilized savage. <br>
<br>
Oblivious to her own state of disarray, she glares contemptously at the woman.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's about time one of you came out here to meet me. I've been waiting for a proper welcome for some time now. In Athens I would be sitting before a warm fire already.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenchiara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Chiara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#993300>(10/5/02 12:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm55.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cslrwillow/images/chiarasig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Temporary Guest</span><hr size=1> Chiara's first thought is that this is going to be fun...  She steps just close enough to Moirai to make the girl uncomfortable, and looks her up and down.<br>
<br>
&quot;In the servants' quarters, perhaps.  I am Queen Chiara, of this tribe.  Understand one thing, girl: if you endanger even one of my women, I will send you back to your temple a failure.  No, that isn't exactly right.  Your own behavior will have made you a failure.&quot;   Satisfied with that statement, Chiara indicates the path they will follow to Marpesia.<br>
<br>
&quot;As for why no one had been sent to meet you... you're an adult wether you act like it or not.  There are also several Queens of other tribes present, and frankly compared with them you aren't all that important a visitor.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Queen is fully aware that what she's said will anger Moirai.  It's also the first step in Chiara's method of breaking down a badly formed ego so a truer one can be built.  She starts down the path, not looking to see if Moirai is following or not.  <br>
